<p>GDP growth: 7.0% GDP: $52bn (PPP: $106bn) Inflation: 14.0% Population: 29.7m GDP per head: $1,760 (PPP: $3,550)</p>

<p>The only credible threat to the rule of Islam Karimov in 2012 will come from his maker, as the ageing autocrat's health wanes. With no clear succession plan in place, this would be severely disruptive, but failing divine intervention the outlook is for political and economic continuity. Demand from Russia and high global prices for Uzbekistan's raw-material exports, including gold, gas and cotton, will drive the economy to a stellar year, although the government has a habit of exaggerating the growth rate.</p>

